<div id=3D"sites-canvas-main" class=3D"sites-canvas-main">
<div id=3D"sites-canvas-main-content">
<table xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" cellspacing=3D"0" class=3D"si=
tes-layout-name-one-column sites-layout-hbox"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"sites=
-layout-tile sites-tile-name-content-1"><div dir=3D"ltr"><div>As I mentione=
d in my previous post the capabilities in Intel provided SD-based Linux ima=
ge is somehow limited. Fortunately the image is built using <a href=3D"http=
s://web.archive.org/web/20150401143438/http://www.yoctoproject.org/">Yocto =
Project</a> embedded Linux build system and Intel provides all files necess=
ary to rebuild the Linux image. Here I will describe how to do that.<br></d=
iv><div><h2><a name=3D"TOC-Prerequisites"></a><b><span style=3D"font-weight=
:normal">Prerequisites</span></b></h2><ul><li>Intel Galileo Board (well, no=
t really needed for the build process, but you want to run the image somewh=
ere, right?). Update the boards' firmware. Older firmware has a bug that pr=
events booting from SD card.<br></li><li>A computer with a fairly new Linux=
 distribution installed on it. I used Ubuntu 12.04.</li><li>Development too=
ls, GCC compiler, etc. You'll also need 7zip utility. Debian/Ubuntu people =
do: <div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><b><span style=
=3D"font-family:times new roman,serif"><code>sudo apt-get install build-ess=
ential p7zip-full</code></span></b></div></li><li>70GB or so available spac=
e on the hard drive.</li><li>Fairly fast Internet connection. It is going t=
o download all the sources required for the image from the Internet.</li><l=
i>A few hours to complete the build process. This will depend on the perfor=
mance of your computer and the Internet connection speed.</li></ul><h2><a n=
ame=3D"TOC-Basic-Steps-to-Rebuild-The-Image"></a><b><span style=3D"font-wei=
ght:normal">Basic Steps to Rebuild The Image</span></b></h2><ol><li>Create =
a directory you'll be using for the build process. Do not use spaces in the=
 directory name. Yocto doesn't like them. <br></li><li>Download "<i>Board S=
upport Package Sources for Intel Quark</i>" from <a href=3D"https://web.arc=
hive.org/web/20150401143438/https://communities.intel.com/community/makers/=
software/drivers">https://communities.intel.com/community/makers/software/d=
rivers</a>. And copy it to your build directory. In my case the file was na=
med <i>Board_Support_Package_Sources_for_Intel_Quark_v0.7.5.7z.</i></li><li=
>Unzip the file: <b><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"><div =
class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>7z x Board_Support_=
Package_Sources_for_Intel_Quark_v0.7.5.7z</code></div></span></b></li><li>U=
nzip <i>meta-clanton_v0.7.5.tar.gz</i>: <b><span style=3D"font-family:couri=
er new,monospace"><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><c=
ode>tar xzvf Board_Support_Package_Sources_for_Intel_Quark_v0.7.5/meta-clan=
ton_v0.7.5.tar.gz</code></div></span></b></li><li>Change directory to <i>me=
ta-clanton_v0.7.5</i>: <b><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"=
><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>cd meta-clant=
on_v0.7.5</code></div></span></b></li><li>Run <i>setup.sh</i>: <b><span sty=
le=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"><div class=3D"sites-codeblock site=
s-codesnippet-block"><code>./setup.sh</code></div></span></b></li><li>Sourc=
e <i>poky/oe-init-build-env</i> script, giving it the build directory (<i>y=
octo_build</i>) as a parameter: <b><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,m=
onospace"><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>sour=
ce poky/oe-init-build-env yocto_build</code></div></span></b></li><li>Run <=
i>bitbake</i> to build the image: <div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codes=
nippet-block"><b><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"><code>bi=
tbake image-full</code></span></b></div></li><ul><li> Note: <i>image-full <=
/i>- SD card image, image-spi - SPI flash image.<br></li></ul><li>Wait seve=
ral hours, and if everything goes well you'll get your image in <i>tmp/depl=
oy/images/</i> directory. It will include:</li><ul><li>The Linux kernel: <i=
>bzImage--3.8-r0-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.bin</i> (YYYYMMDDhhmmss - timestamp=
 indicating the build start time)<br></li><li>Initial RAM FS: <i>core-image=
-minimal-initramfs-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.rootfs.cpio.gz</i></li><li>File s=
ystem image: <i>image-full-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.rootfs.ext3</i><br></li><=
li>Kernel modules: <i>modules--3.8-r0-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.tgz</i> (not r=
eally needed, they are already in the file system image)<br></li><li>Grub c=
onfiguration: <i>boot/grub/grub.conf</i><br></li></ul><li>Copy these files =
to SD card renaming files as follows (resulting paths are relative to SD ca=
rd's root):</li><ul><li><i>bzImage--3.8-r0-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.bin -&gt;=
 bzImage</i></li><li><i>core-image-minimal-initramfs-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss=
.rootfs.cpio.gz -&gt; core-image-minimal-initramfs-clanton.cpio.gz</i></li>=
<li><i>image-full-clanton-YYYYMMDDhhmmss.rootfs.ext3 -&gt; image-full-clant=
on.ext3</i></li><li><i>boot/grub/grub.conf -&gt; boot/grub/grub.conf<br></i=
></li><li>Note that you can keep names or use different names for all files=
 except of the <i>image-full-clanton.ext3</i>, and just update <i>grub.conf=
</i> with the correct names. The file system image must be named <i>image-f=
ull-clanton.ext3</i> (initramfs will look for that) unless you update the c=
onfiguration.</li></ul><li>Insert SD card to your Galileo board, reboot it,=
 and enjoy!</li></ol><h2><a name=3D"TOC-Building-Linux-Standard-Base-LSB-Im=
age"></a><b><span style=3D"font-weight:normal">Building Linux Standard Base=
 (LSB) Image</span></b></h2></div><div>In my case I wanted to get an LSB (L=
inux Standard Base) compatible image, with development tools installed on i=
t, and USB audio support. I choose to use Poky <i>core-image-lsb-sdk</i> im=
age profile as it includes all the stuff I needed. (Poky is a Yocto project=
 reference distribution.) <br><br></div><div>The instructions below assume =
that you already done steps 1 - 7 above, and you are in <i>meta-clanton_v0.=
7.5/yocto_build/</i> directory.<br></div><div><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Update-loc=
al.conf"></a>Update local.conf</h3></div><div></div><div>Edit <i>conf/local=
.conf</i>. We will want to use to use eglibc instead of uClibc (LSB require=
s eglibc/glibc). Set DISTRO to <i>clanton-full</i>:<br><span style=3D"font-=
family:courier new,monospace"><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnipp=
et-block"><code>DISTRO ?=3D "<b>clanton-full</b>"</code></div></span> Note =
that supplied Arduino IDE cross compiles sketches with uClibc and they will=
 not work with eglibc.<br><br></div><div>You might also want to tweak BB_NU=
MBER_THREADS and PARALLEL_MAKE variables. Increase numbers if you have a co=
mputer with many cores or processors to speed up compilation process. I wou=
ld recommend having 2-3 threads per core. The default configuration is OK f=
or a dual or quad core processor system.<br><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Comment-out-=
uClibc-patch-for-v4l2apps"></a>Comment out uClibc patch for v4l2apps</h3></=
div><div>Edit <i>../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-multimedia/v4l2apps/v4l-uti=
ls_0.8.8.bbappend</i>, prepend each line with a hash (#) sign:<br></div><di=
v><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"><div class=3D"sites-cod=
eblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code><b>#</b>FILESEXTRAPATHS_prepend :=3D =
"${THISDIR}/files:"</code><br><code><b>#</b>SRC_URI +=3D "file://uclibc-ena=
ble.patch"</code><br><code><b>#</b>DEPENDS +=3D "libiconv"</code></div></sp=
an></div><div><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Create-recipe-for-the-image"></a>Create re=
cipe for the image</h3><p>Copy <i>../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/image=
s/image-full.bb</i>&nbsp; file to <i>../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/im=
ages/image-sdk.bb</i>:</p><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-b=
lock"><b><code>cp </code><code>../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/images/i=
mage-full.bb to ../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/images/image-sdk.bb</co=
de></b></div><p>Edit ../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/images/image-sdk.b=
b file. Append <i>packagegroup-core-basic packagegroup-core-lsb kernel-dev<=
/i> to IMAGE_INSTALL:<br></p><p>
</p><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><p><span style=
=3D"font-family:courier new,monospace"><code>IMAGE_INSTALL
 =3D "packagegroup-core-boot ${ROOTFS_PKGMANAGE_BOOTSTRAP}=20
${CORE_IMAGE_EXTRA_INSTALL}<b> packagegroup-core-basic=20
packagegroup-core-lsb kernel-dev</b>"</code></span></p></div><br>Append <i>=
tools-sdk dev-pkgs tools-debug eclipse-debug tools-profile tools-testapps d=
ebug-tweaks</i> to IMAGE_FEATURES:<br><span style=3D"font-family:courier ne=
w,monospace"><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>I=
MAGE_FEATURES +=3D "package-management <b>tools-sdk dev-pkgs tools-debug ec=
lipse-debug tools-profile tools-testapps debug-tweaks</b>"</code></div></sp=
an><p>You might also want to increase root file system size from the 300 MB=
 default to 3 GB or so. If configured as described here image will use abou=
t 1.5GB so with 3 GB you'll have plenty of space for other things.<br></p><=
div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>IMAGE_ROOTFS_SI=
ZE =3D "<b>3072000</b>"</code></div><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Other-Changes"></a>O=
ther Changes</h3><p>I made a couple more tweaks to the image. First is an u=
pdate to Galileo kernel patch to fix an issue with CY8C9540A I/O expander. =
By default intel_cln_gip module configures Intel Quark to use I2C fast mode=
, and CY8C9540A doesn't want to work with that mode. So the change is to ma=
ke standard mode default. Find <i>+static unsigned int i2c_std_mode;</i> li=
ne in <i>../meta-clanton-bsp/recipes-kernel/linux/files/clanton.patch</i> f=
ile and assign 1 to that variable (add <i>=3D 1</i> before semicolon):</p><=
div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><code>+static unsigne=
d int i2c_std_mode <b>=3D 1</b>;</code></div><p>Another patch is to allow c=
onfigurable file system image file name. So that I can have multiple file s=
ystem images on one SD card, and switch between them easily using GRUB menu=
. The patch is attached to this blog (rootimage.patch). Copy it to <i>../me=
ta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/initrdscripts/files/</i> directory and add <=
i>SRC_URI +=3D "file://rootimage.patch;patchdir=3D${WORKDIR}"</i> line to <=
i>../meta-clanton-distro/recipes-core/initrdscripts/initramfs-live-boot_1.0=
.bbappend</i> file:</p><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-bloc=
k"><code>FILESEXTRAPATHS_prepend :=3D "${THISDIR}/files:"</code><br><code>S=
RC_URI +=3D "file://name.patch;patchdir=3D${WORKDIR}"</code><br><b><code>SR=
C_URI +=3D "file://rootimage.patch;patchdir=3D${WORKDIR}"</code></b></div><=
p>Once this patch is applied you can use <i>rootimage=3D&lt;filename&gt;.ex=
t3</i> option in the kernel command line in grub.conf to specify the root f=
ile system image file name. For example:</p><div class=3D"sites-codeblock s=
ites-codesnippet-block"><code>title Clanton SDK</code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp; root (hd0,0)</code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; kernel /bzImage--3.=
8-r0-clanton-20131027083753.bin root=3D/dev/ram0 console=3DttyS1,115200n8 e=
arlycon=3Duart8250,mmio32,0x8010f000,115200n8 reboot=3Defi,warm apic=3Ddebu=
g rw LABEL=3Dboot debugshell=3D5 <b>rootimage=3Dimage-sdk-clanton-201310270=
83753.rootfs.ext3</b></code><br><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; initrd /core-image=
-minimal-initramfs-clanton-20131027083753.rootfs.cpio.gz</code><br></div><h=
3><a name=3D"TOC-Reconfigure-kernel-enable-whatever-features-you-like"></a>=
<span style=3D"font-weight:normal"><b>Reconfigure kernel, enable whatever f=
eatures you like</b><br></span></h3></div><div><div class=3D"sites-codebloc=
k sites-codesnippet-block"><b><span style=3D"font-family:courier new,monosp=
ace"><code>bitbake linux-yocto-clanton -c menuconfig</code></span></b></div=
> </div><div></div><div><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Build-the-image"></a><b><span st=
yle=3D"font-weight:normal"><b>Build the image</b><br></span></b></h3></div>=
<div><div class=3D"sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block"><b><code>bitbak=
e image-sdk</code></b></div> </div><div></div><div><p>For information more =
information on available image profiles, see the "<a href=3D"https://web.ar=
chive.org/web/20150401143438/http://www.yoctoproject.org/docs/1.5/ref-manua=
l/ref-manual.html#ref-images">Images</a>" chapter in the Yocto Project Refe=
rence Manual.</p><h3><a name=3D"TOC-Install-the-image"></a><b><span style=
=3D"font-weight:normal"><b>Install the image</b><br></span></b></h3><p>Foll=
ow steps 9 - 11 above to install the image on the SD card.</p><h3><a name=
=3D"TOC-Files-and-patches"></a>Files and patches</h3><p>For your convenienc=
e I attached a tarball which includes files with all the modifications desc=
ribed above and my kernel configuration with USB audio enabled. You can sim=
ply unpack it in to your build directory (one with <i>meta-clanton_v0.7.5/<=
/i> directory). <br></p></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>=20
</div>=20
